edleston, Derbyshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Kedleston, Derbyshire, England":"Kedleston, Derbyshire, England"},"en":{"1299–1380":"1299–1380","1300–Male":"1300–Deceased","1301–Female":"1301–Deceased","1315–1406":"1315–1406","1319–1406":"1319–1406","1270–1330":"1270–1330","1275–1335":"1275–1335","Abt 1315":"about 1315","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","1380":"1380","1270":"1270","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1301":"1301","about 1317":"about 1317","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1319":"1319","1406":"1406","Kedleston,Derbyshire,England.":"Kedleston, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom","Kedleston, Derbyshire, England":"Kedleston, Derbyshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Curzon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Notre-Dame-de-Courson in Calvados, France, which was named with the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Curtius</i> (from <i>curtus</i> ‘short’) + the locative suffix <i>-o</i>, genitive <i>-onis</i>. There is also a place called Curzon in Vendée, but this is not the source of the English surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Curson","meanings":["English (Norfolk): variant of   Curzon  ."]}]},{"name":"Roger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name, <i>Rog(i)er</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger Curzon was born in 1299, in Kedleston, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard Curzon, was 29 and his mother, Joan, was 24. He married Joan about 1317, in Kedleston, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1380, in his hometown, at the age of 81."},"et":{"1299–1380":"1299–1380","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1301–Female":"1301–Surnud","1315–1406":"1315–1406","1319–1406":"1319–1406","1270–1330":"1270–1330","1275–1335":"1275–1335","Abt 1315":"umbes 1315","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","1380":"1380","1270":"1270","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1301":"1301","about 1317":"umbes 1317","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1319":"1319","1406":"1406","Kedleston,Derbyshire,England.":"Kedleston, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kedleston, Derbyshire, England":"Kedleston, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"1299–1380":"1299–1380","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1301–Female":"1301–Kuollut","1315–1406":"1315–1406","1319–1406":"1319–1406","1270–1330":"1270–1330","1275–1335":"1275–1335","Abt 1315":"noin 1315","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","1380":"1380","1270":"1270","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1301":"1301","about 1317":"noin 1317","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1319":"1319","1406":"1406","Kedleston,Derbyshire,England.":"Kedleston, Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kedleston, Derbyshire, England":"Kedleston, Derbyshire, England"},"fr":{"1299–1380":"1299–1380","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1301–Female":"1301–Décédée","1315–1406":"1315–1406","1319–1406":"1319–1406","1270–1330":"1270–1330","1275–1335":"1275–1335","Abt 1315":"environ 1315","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","1380":"1380","1270":"1270","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1301":"1301","about 1317":"environ 1317","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1319":"1319","1406":"1406","Kedlest